          "text": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": {
                "text": "A group of young people came together over the summer of 2015 to explore the theme of human emotions.",
                "spans": []
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": {
                "text": "Using The Book of Human Emotions by Tiffany Watt-Smith as a starting point, the group identified emotions that intrigued them. They learnt radio-making skills with support from facilitator Grace Huber to create a suite of 4 short audio pieces which will are available below.",
                "spans": [
                  {
                    "start": 6,
                    "end": 32,
                    "type": "hyperlink",
                    "data": {
                      "link_type": "Web",
                      "url": "https://wellcomecollection.org/book-human-emotions"
                    }
                  },
                  {
                    "start": 6,
                    "end": 32,
                    "type": "em",
                    "data": {}
                  }
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": {
                "text": "The audio pieces were made available in a ‘listening lounge’, where visitors were encouraged to spend some time relaxing, listening and sharing some of their own experiences.",
                "spans": []
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "heading2",
              "content": {
                "text": "Part of RawMinds",
                "spans": [
                  {
                    "start": 8,
                    "end": 16,
